text: Many is the parish seat of Sabine Parish, Louisiana, United States. As of the 2020 Census, 2,571 people lived in Many. This is a decrease of 135 from the 2010 Census. The town was named for James B. Many, a commander of nearby Fort Jesup. == References == Category:Settlements in Sabine Parish, Louisiana Category:Towns in Louisiana Category:Parish seats in Louisiana
title: Many, Louisiana
